GCC-based features maintain reasonable performance, confirming their robustness to acoustic variability, while IPD and Log-Mel show degradation since they are more sensitive to environmental changes, highlighting the superior robustness of time-delay features over phase-based and spectral representations. \newline

\noindent
The combined feature set (All Features) achieves the best overall performance in both scenarios. This demonstrates that multi-feature fusion enhances robustness and generalization by leveraging complementary information across time-delay, phase, and spectral domains, effectively mitigating individual feature weaknesses.

