\subsection{Encountered Problems and Proposed Solutions}
Throughout the project journey, the team encountered several technical and management challenges that required collaboration, leadership, and continuous problem solving.
One of the main technical challenges was integrating different modules developed separately using different tools and libraries. The sound recognition, localization, and speech-to-text components initially operated independently. To solve this issue, the team proposed a unified architecture where each subsystem runs as a service under one central processing framework, allowing all outputs to work together in real time.
Another challenge was hardware limitations on embedded platforms such as Raspberry Pi, especially when running multiple AI models simultaneously. This created delays in inference and system responsiveness. The solution was to optimize processing pipelines, load models only once during startup, reduce repeated computations, and use lightweight pretrained models suitable for edge devices.
Noise and environmental variability also affected system performance. Some sounds were harder to classify at long distances or in noisy rooms, and speech recognition accuracy decreased in challenging conditions. To overcome this, the team improved preprocessing, selected confidence thresholds, and recommended future fine-tuning using real-world local datasets.Another challenge involved designing a user interface that remained clear and readable while displaying multiple real-time outputs simultaneously. Early interface versions contained excessive information and directional indicators that required refinement. This issue was addressed by redesigning the layout, introducing Detailed and Light modes, simplifying visual elements, and improving synchronization between sound recognition results, speech captions, and directional alerts.\newline

\noindent
From a teamwork perspective, coordinating tasks among multiple students and managing shared report files required careful communication. To avoid losing edits or duplicating work, team members continuously informed each other before modifying shared files, saved backup copies, and updated the latest version after each contribution.
Time management was another challenge due to simultaneous deadlines for experiments, implementation, and report submission. This was addressed by dividing responsibilities clearly, setting internal deadlines, and tracking weekly progress. These experiences demonstrated strong teamwork, leadership, and collaborative engineering practice.

